@TITLE "tapeconv(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name tapeconv - Sinclair ZX Spectrum tape file convertor @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}tapeconv@{"ub"} [-i @{"i"}format@{"ui"}]@{"i"}@{"ui"} [-o @{"i"}format@{"ui"}]@{"i"}@{"ui"} @{"i"}tapefile@{"ui"} @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description Tapeconv converts between ZX Spectrum tape images. It reads in one tape file and writes the converted file to standard output. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Options @{"i"}-i@{"ui"} format specifies the format of the input tape file. Generally, this will be autodetcted but you can use <@{"i"}tzx@{"ui"}<@{"i"}@{"ui"} or <@{"i"}tap@{"ui"}<@{"i"}@{"ui"} to force .tzx or .tap format respectively. @{"i"}-o@{"ui"} format specifies the format of the output tape file in the same way as the @{"i"}-i@{"ui"} option. This will default to .tzx format if it is not specified. Note that .tap format is a subset of .tzx format, and hence the conversion may not succeed. Warning messages will be given in this case. @{"i"}tapefile@{"ui"} specifies a tape file (in a format supported by @{" " link "'libspectrum.3'/MAIN"}@{"i"}libspectrum@{"ui"}(3) ) to be converted. @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}Bugs None known. @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'fuse.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'fuse-utils.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse-utils@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'libspectrum.3'/MAIN"}@{"i"}libspectrum@{"ui"}(3) , @{" " link "'listbasic.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}listbasic@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'tzxlist.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}tzxlist@{"ui"}(1) 

The comp.sys.sinclair Spectrum FAQ, at 
@{" " link "'http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html.guide/MAIN"}@{"i"}http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html@{"ui"}. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Author Philip Kendall (philip-fuse@shadowmagic.org.uk). 


